    title: 'Governor faces recall effort over controversial education policy',
    author: 'Lisa Monroe', date: 'March 14, 2026', readTime: 5,
    image: 'https://picsum.photos/id/180/900/500', imageCredit: 'State Government Photo',
    body: `<p>A well-funded recall campaign has been launched against the governor of a western state following the implementation of sweeping changes to the state's public education curriculum that have divided parents, teachers, and lawmakers.</p>
    <p>The policy, which restructures K-12 standards across multiple subjects, was enacted through executive order after the state legislature failed to pass the governor's education reform package during the last session.</p>
    <p>"This is government overreach at its worst," said the campaign's lead organizer. "These decisions should be made by parents, teachers, and elected representatives — not by executive decree."</p>
    <p>Supporters of the governor counter that the reforms are necessary to address declining test scores and prepare students for a rapidly changing economy. "Sometimes leadership means making tough decisions," a spokesperson for the governor said. "The status quo was failing our children."</p>
    <p>The recall campaign has until June to collect the required 500,000 signatures to trigger a special election. Organizers say they have already gathered more than 200,000 in the first three weeks.</p>`
